虽然柬埔寨是世界上[[森林開伐|森林開伐率]]最高的国家之一，但波哥猪笼草的分布地的环境还相对未受破坏。<ref name=bokor />当时，弗朗索瓦·梅依据[[世界自然保护联盟|世界自然保护联盟]]的标准，认为波哥猪笼草“潜在易危”。<ref name=bokor />虽然波哥猪笼草生长于波哥国家公园中，但其仍然受到当地旅游业发展的威胁。柬埔寨政府已将波哥山租赁予私人以修建度假村和[[高尔夫|高尔夫]]球场。<ref name=bokor />虽然开发商表示会重视环境保护，但波哥山上仍有大片的森林遭到破坏。<ref name="看看新闻网">{{cite web| url=http://world.kankanews.com/vods/ff80808129b4c37e0129b77473cb007a/ff8080812d9ea042012da22f1f740509/| title=波哥猪笼草面临灭绝危险| publisher=看看新闻网| date=2011-01-20| accessdate=2011-06-19}}{{dead link|date=2018年3月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>“波哥城”项目建设使波哥猪笼草的原生地加速消亡。<ref name=con1>Mey, F.S. 2011. [http://carnivorousockhom.blogspot.com/2011/08/works-on-phnom-bokor-2011.html Works on Phnom Bokor. 2011] {{Wayback|url=http://carnivorousockhom.blogspot.com/2011/08/works-on-phnom-bokor-2011.html |date=20120322181056 }}. ''Strange Fruits: A Garden's Chronicle'', August 29, 2011.</ref><ref name=con2>Mey, F.S. 2011. [http://carnivorousockhom.blogspot.com/2011/08/bokor-city-project.html The "Bokor City" project] {{Wayback|url=http://carnivorousockhom.blogspot.com/2011/08/bokor-city-project.html |date=20120322181059 }}. ''Strange Fruits: A Garden's Chronicle'', August 29, 2011.</ref><ref>Worrell, S. & P. Seangly 2012. [http://www.phnompenhpost.com/index.php/2012031655065/National-news/city-on-a-hill-sparks-little-talk.html City on a hill sparks little talk] {{Wayback|url=http://www.phnompenhpost.com/index.php/2012031655065/National-news/city-on-a-hill-sparks-little-talk.html |date=20120423060338 }}. ''The Phnom Penh Post'', March 16, 2012.</ref>截至2011年，波哥猪笼草的模式产地及新发现的原生地都依然受到当地不断开发的威胁。<ref name=con1 /><ref name=con2 />

